Spatial spreading model and dynamics of West Nile virus in birds and mosquitoes with free boundary (Zhigui Lin - 22 March, 2017)
In this paper, a reaction-diffusion system is proposed to model the spatial spreading of West Nile virus in vector mosquitoes and host birds in North America. Our results suggest that the virus will be in a scenario of vanishing if $R_0\leq 1$, and the virus will spread to the whole region if $R_{0}^F(t_0)\geq 1$ for some $t_0\geq 0$, while if $R^F_0(0)<1<R_0$, the spreading or vanishing of the virus depends on the initial numbers of infected mosquitoes and birds, the area of the infected region and diffusion rates
